paragraphs.title: What is the average distance and average payment by car/vehicle
paragraphs.text:
%sql

SELECT vehicle_id, 
    mean(trip_distance) as avg_distance, 
    mean(payment_amount) as avg_payment 
    FROM rawdata_sql 
    GROUP BY vehicle_id 
    ORDER BY avg_distance DESC 
    LIMIT 10

paragraphs.title: Display Descriptive Stats for Numerical Data
Transform Data / Extract Entities
paragraphs.text:
%spark.r


transformed1 <- selectExpr(rawdata, 
                            "vehicle_id",
                            "pickup_datetime",
                            "pickup_latitude",
                            "pickup_longitude",
                            "trip_distance",
                            "passenger_count",
                            "dropoff_datetime",
                            "dropoff_latitude",
                            "dropoff_longitude",
                            "fare_amount",
                            "tolls_amount",
                            "taxes_amount",
                            "tip_amount",
                            "payment_amount",
                            "cast(split(split(pickup_datetime,' ')[0],'/')[1] as int) pickup_day",
                            "cast(split(split(pickup_datetime,' ')[1],':')[0] as int) pickup_hour"
                            )

schema(transformed1)
showDF(transformed1)

paragraphs.title: Model Prep
paragraphs.text:
%spark.r

# Split into Training and Testing DFs
df_training_testing <- randomSplit(transformed1, weights=c(0.8, 0.2), seed=12345)

trainingDF <- df_training_testing[[1]]
testingDF  <- df_training_testing[[2]]

count(trainingDF)
count(testingDF)

paragraphs.title: Modeling (GLM)
paragraphs.text:
%spark.r

# Family may include (https://stat.ethz.ch/R-manual/R-devel/library/stats/html/family.html): 
#    binomial(link = "logit")
#    gaussian(link = "identity")
#    Gamma(link = "inverse")
#    inverse.gaussian(link = "1/mu^2")
#    poisson(link = "log")
#    quasi(link = "identity", variance = "constant")
#    quasibinomial(link = "logit")
#    quasipoisson(link = "log")

gaussianGLM <- spark.glm(trainingDF, trip_distance ~ passenger_count + fare_amount + tolls_amount + tip_amount, family = "gaussian")

# Model summary
summary(gaussianGLM)

# Prediction
gaussianPredictions <- predict(gaussianGLM, testingDF)

#showDF(select(gaussianPredictions, "label","prediction")

createOrReplaceTempView(gaussianPredictions, "gaussianPredictions_sql")
